# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
# BriefingClaw — Environment Configuration
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
#
# !! DO NOT COMMIT YOUR REAL .env FILE TO VERSION CONTROL !!
# !! The .gitignore excludes .env — keep it that way.     !!
#
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your keys.
# Only ONE frontier provider is required — pick the one you have.
# The local model (Granite via Podman AI Lab) needs no key.
#
# Usage: cp env.example .env && nano .env
# ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# FRONTIER MODEL PROVIDER (pick one — used by research agents)
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# Option A: Anthropic (Claude)
ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
FRONTIER_PROVIDER=anthropic
FRONTIER_MODEL=claude-sonnet-4-20250514

# Option B: OpenAI (GPT)
# OPENAI_API_KEY=
# FRONTIER_PROVIDER=openai
# FRONTIER_MODEL=gpt-4o

# Option C: Google (Gemini)
# GOOGLE_API_KEY=
# FRONTIER_PROVIDER=google
# FRONTIER_MODEL=gemini-2.0-flash

# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# LOCAL MODEL (served by Podman AI Lab — no key needed)
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
LOCAL_MODEL_URL=http://127.0.0.1:8001/v1
LOCAL_MODEL_ID=granite-8b
LOCAL_MODEL_KEY=not-needed

# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# WEB SEARCH (required for Sherlock Ohms and Bloom-borg)
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Get a free key at https://tavily.com (1000 searches/month)
TAVILY_API_KEY=

# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# MODEL ROUTING — which agents use which model
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Frontier model (cloud): complex reasoning, web research
#   → Oprah-tor (orchestration), Sherlock Ohms (exec research),
#     Bloom-borg (account intel)
#
# Local model (Granite on laptop): structured tasks, private data
#   → Déjà View (CAB history), Draft Punk (doc assembly),
#     Alfred Bitworth (VVIP protocol)
#
# Why this split?
#   Research agents need frontier-class reasoning + web search.
#   Data agents work with YOUR files — they never leave the laptop.
#   This is the enterprise pattern: power where you need it,
#   privacy where it matters.
# ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
